    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kimberly</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Central America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1891</hi>.</date>
                            (Received February 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 239.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Learning a new minister for our Government is
                        to presently appear here, I have the honor to suggest that while peace and
                        tranquillity are at present reigning that he be advised to arrange, if
                        possible, a better and safer system of telegraphic communication with our
                        home Government at Washington. These telegraphic lines being under the
                        ownership and surveillance of this Government should make them all the more
                        amenable under our treaty laws for the safe conduct, prompt and easy access
                        to and from your agents here.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Samuel Kimberly</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad int</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
